  "prompt": "What are the top 10 most read articles on Wikipedia?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Wikipedia does not publicly release a definitive, real-time ranking of its most-read articles. However, based on historical data, trends, and Wikimedia Foundation reports, some of the most consistently popular articles on Wikipedia include those related to major global events, historical figures, popular culture, and general topics of broad interest. Here are some categories and examples of articles that are often among the most read:\n\n### 1. **Global Events and News**\n   - Articles related to major events like pandemics (e.g., **COVID-19**), wars (e.g., **World War II**), or natural disasters often see spikes in readership.\n\n### 2. **Historical Figures**\n   - **Adolf Hitler**\n   - **Barack Obama**\n   - **Donald Trump**\n\n### 3. **Popular Culture**\n   - **List of Pok\u00e9mon**\n   - **Game of Thrones**\n   - **Marvel Cinematic Universe**\n\n### 4. **General Knowledge**\n   - **United States**\n   - **Earth**\n   - **Human**\n\n### 5. **Technology**\n   - **iPhone**\n   - **Google**\n   - **Elon Musk**\n\n### 6. **Science and Nature**\n   - **Quantum mechanics**\n   - **Theory of relativity**\n   - **Extinction events**\n\n### 7. **Sports**\n   - **Cristiano Ronaldo**\n   - **Lionel Messi**\n   - **FIFA World Cup**\n\n### 8. **Geography**\n   - **India**\n   - **China**\n   - **Europe**\n\n### 9. **Mythology and Religion**\n   - **Greek mythology**\n   - **Bible**\n   - **Islam**\n\n### 10. **Health and Medicine**\n   - **Vaccines**\n   - **Mental health**\n   - **Cancer**\n\n### Notes:\n- The popularity of articles can fluctuate based on current events, cultural trends, and time of year.\n- Wikimedia occasionally publishes insights into the most-viewed articles during specific events or time frames (e.g., during the COVID-19 pandemic, articles on the virus and related topics saw a massive surge in traffic).\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, you can check Wikimedia\u2019s official tools like **Pageviews Analysis** or third-party platforms that track Wikipedia traffic.",
